Say hello to the sensational return of Lavender - the newest addition to our permanent menu!

reviews_data.review_text: Ok first the coffee was pretty decent once we got it. The service was mixed. The gentleman at the counter was pleasant and competent. The bad-  They had run out of a number of food menu items. One of the main notable things gs was the attitude of the barista making drinks. She refused to make 6 large coffees for the man in front of us saying they did not have the capacity to do that, the manner in which she was talking was rude by all accounts. On our order, she closed it as fulfilled before we even got our coffees. She had another person ask for something and she was very direct and unfriendly to them as well. Overall just not a good impression as we sat and watched what was going on.

reviews_data.review_text: Was so excited to get a Caribou Coffee (much better than Starbucks in my opinion)  but the first experience was meh. Drinks were okay but not great (I’ll attribute that to new store and employees). However, the menu lists only Medium drinks and pricing. When I ordered two drinks, I did not specify a size and was not asked. When I pulled around, my bill was much higher than expected. They had rung me up for an extra-large by default without asking. Like most places, the XL just means a ton more ice. I see that as a pretty unethical way of doing business. If you go here, make sure you specify what size you want or they’ll assume what’s most beneficial for their bottom-line. I won’t be back for a while.

reviews_data.review_text: Was so excited to get a Caribou Coffee (much better than Starbucks in my opinion)  but the first experience was meh. Drinks were okay but not great (I’ll attribute that to new store and employees). However, the menu lists only Medium drinks and pricing. When I ordered two drinks, I did not specify a size and was not asked. When I pulled around, my bill was much higher than expected. They had rung me up for an extra-large by default without asking. Like most places, the XL just means a ton more ice. I see that as a pretty unethical way of doing business. If you go here, make sure you specify what size you want or they’ll assume what’s most beneficial for their bottom-line. I won’t be back for a while.

Honestly one of the best coffee shops I've been to. Employees are incredibly caring to customers and it's very refreshing to see.
The food and coffee I've gotten have been flavorful each time I have stopped by.

Service itself is quick.

10/10
